<BLOCK2><N>(b)</N><TI><UNDER>ASSESSMENTS UNDER APPEAL</UNDER></TI>
<P>2. The Appellant appeals from the following:
<P1>a. Notice of Reassessment issued for the Appellant's 2007 taxation year on November 23, 2015; and</P1>
<P1>b. Notice of Confirmation issued for the Appellant's 2008 taxation year on October 14, 2015.</P1></P>
<P>3. The Appellant objected to Notices of Reassessment issued May 28, 2010 by Notice of Objection filed on August 12, 2010. The Minister issued Notice of Reassessment dated November 23, 2015 for the 2007 taxation year and Notice of Confirmation dated October 14, 2015 for the 2008 taxation year after considering the Appellant's Notice of Objection.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>(c)</N><TI><UNDER>FACTS</UNDER></TI>
<P>4. The Appellant works in the area of executive search and placement. The Appellant is the chairman of Mandrake Management Consultants Corporation (&ldquo;Mandrake Consultants&rdquo;). The Appellant did not own a controlling interest in Mandrake Consultants and important decisions were made together with all of the corporation's owners.</P>
<P>5. The Appellant develops his executive and placement business by building deep relationships with his clients.</P>
<P>6. Among many others, the Appellant has had a business relationship with The Hive Strategic Marketing Inc. (&ldquo;The Hive&rdquo;) whereby the Appellant recruits employees for The Hive.</P>
<P>7. The Appellant has had a close business relationship with The Hive and its predecessor for over 22 years. The relationship began when the Appellant recruited a president for The Hive in 1993. The Appellant estimates that the recruitment business relationship with The Hive has generated over two million dollars in revenue.</P>
<P>8. Mandrake Consultants reported all income received from the executive search and placement services performed for The Hive.</P>
<P>9. The Hive is in the business of providing marketing services to large companies. The Hive's business requires that its employees travel around the world to stage events and parties. The purpose of the events and parties is to promote its clients' businesses.</P>
<BLOCK3><TI><UNDER>2007</UNDER></TI>
<P>10. The Appellant's spouse, Robin Peerenboom, owned a condominium located at XXXXXXXXXX (&ldquo;Sloans Curve&rdquo;).</P>
<P>11. Ms. Peerenboom rented Sloans Curve to The Hive since 2004. Ms. Peerenboom received the rent in $62,500 U.S. dollars approximately equal to $66,875 Canadian in 2007.</P>
<P>12. Ms. Peerenboom reported the rent she received from The Hive as rental income in her 2007 return.</P>
<P>13. The Hive paid the rent for Sloans Curve to the Appellant, who received the rent on behalf of Ms. Peerenboom.</P>
<P>14. The Hive also paid for other costs related to Sloans Curve to the Appellant. In total, The Hive paid $75,000 Canadian to the Appellant as rent and reimbursement of occupancy costs related to the property.</P>
<P>15. The occupancy costs are broken down as follows:
