<BLOCK2><N>(d)</N><TI><UNDER>ISSUES</UNDER></TI>
<P>49. The issues to be determined are:
<P1>a. whether the Minister properly included $8,125 related to Sloans Curve as unreported income in the Appellant's 2007 taxation year pursuant to ss. 9(1) of the <EM>Income Tax Act</EM>, R.S.C. 1985, as amended (the &ldquo;Act&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>b. whether the Minister properly included $40,867 related to Moongate as unreported income in the Appellant's 2008 taxation year pursuant to ss. 9(1) of the Act;</P1>
<P1>c. whether the Minister properly included $43,816 reimbursed to Mandrake Properties as unreported income in the Appellant's 2008 taxation year pursuant to ss. 9(1) of the Act; and</P1>
<P1>d. whether the Minister properly included $83,619 related to Sloans Curve as unreported income in the Appellant's 2008 taxation year pursuant to ss. 9(1) of the Act.</P1></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>(e)</N><TI><UNDER>STATUTORY PROVISIONS RELIED UPON</UNDER></TI>
<P>50. The Appellant relies, <EM>inter alia</EM>, upon and 9(1) of the Act.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>(f)</N><TI><UNDER>REASONS</UNDER></TI>
<P>51. The Appellant submits that the Minister failed to properly consider that the $8,125 payment from The Hive to Ms. Peerenboom in relation to Sloans Curve in 2007 was a reimbursement of occupancy costs and not income to the Appellant. Furthermore, even if the amount was income, which is not admitted, it should be included in Ms. Peerenboom's income and not in the Appellant's income.</P>
<P>52. The Appellant submits that the Minister failed to properly consider that the $40,867 payment in relation to Moongate in 2008 was a reimbursement to Mandrake Properties for the renovations to Moongate requested by The Hive and not income to the Appellant.</P>
<P>53. The Appellant submits that the Minister failed to properly consider that the $43,816 in relation to travel expenses and Sloan Curve's expenses in 2008 were reimbursements to Mandrake Properties and not income to the Appellant.</P>
<P>54. The Appellant submits that the Minister failed to properly consider that $83,619 in relation to travel expenses and Sloan Curve's expenses in 2008 were reimbursements to Mandrake Properties and not income to the Appellant.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>(g)</N><TI><UNDER>RELIEF SOUGHT</UNDER></TI>
<P>55. The Appellant requests that his appeal be allowed, with costs, and that the matter be referred back to the Minister for reassessment on the basis that the Minister has erred reassessing the Appellant's 2007 and 2008 taxation years to include $8,125 and $168,630, respectively, as unreported income.</P>
<P>56. The Appellant requests such further or other relief as this Honorable Court deems just.</P>
