<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>REPLY</UNDER></TI>
<P>In reply to the Appellant's Notice of Appeal with respect to the 2007 and 2008 taxation years, the Deputy Attorney General of Canada says:</P>
<BLOCK2><N>A.</N><TI>STATEMENT OF FACTS</TI>
<P>1. He admits the allegations of fact stated in paragraphs 1, 2, 3, 6, 9, 13, 17, 18, 37, 42 and 45 of the Notice of Appeal.</P>
<P>2. He denies the allegations of fact stated in paragraph 44 of the Notice of Appeal.</P>
<P>3. He has no knowledge of and therefore puts in issue the allegations of fact stated in paragraphs 5, 7, 8, 10, 11, 12, 14, 15, 16, 19 to 36, 38, 39, 40, 41 and 48 of the Notice of Appeal.</P>
<P>4. With respect to paragraph 4 of the Notice of Appeal, he admits the allegations of fact in the first sentence but has no knowledge of and puts in issue the remaining allegations of fact in this paragraph.</P>
<P>5. He denies paragraph 43 and states that the Minister audited The Hive and found that the <EM>payments</EM> to the Appellant, Mandrake Properties and Ms. Peerenboom were recorded as payments to a consultant.</P>
<P>6. He denies paragraph 46 and states that on May 28, 2010, the Minister issued Notices of Reassessement for the Appellant's 2007 and 2008 taxation years to include the <EM>payments</EM> in the Appellant's income.</P>
<P>7. He denies paragraph 47 and states that the <EM>payments</EM> from the Hive and added to the Appellant's income include the amounts set out in this paragraph.</P>
<P>8. The Minister of National Revenue (the &ldquo;Minister&rdquo;) reassessed the Appellant's tax liability for the 2007 and 2008 years by Notices dated May 28, 2010 to include T4A income from The Hive Strategic Marketing Inc. (the &ldquo;Hive&rdquo;) of $176,755 and $168,302, respectively.</P>
<P>9. The Appellant filed a Notice of Objection on August 12, 2010.</P>
<P>10. By Notice dated October 14, 2015, the Minister varied the reassessment for the 2007 taxation year to remove $168,630 of income and the Minister confirmed the reassessment for the 2008 taxation year.</P>
<P>11. In determining the Appellant's tax liability, the Minister made the following assumptions of fact:
<P1>a) the Appellant provided consulting services to the Hive in the 2007 and 2008 taxation years;</P1>
<P1>b) the Appellant and the Hive arranged so that the Hive would pay for the Appellant's expenses and make upgrades to his Moongate (Ontario) property and his Sloans Curve (Florida) property in exchange for the Appellant's consulting services;</P1>
<P1>c) the Appellant received income from the Hive of $8,125 in the 2007 taxation year; and</P1>
<P1>d) the Appellant received income from the Hive of $168,302 in the 2008 taxation year.</P1></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>B.</N><TI>ISSUES TO BE DECIDED</TI>
<P>12. The issues are:
<P1>a) Whether the Minister properly included $8,125 in the Appellant's income in the 2007 taxation year under section 9(1) of the <EM>Act</EM>.</P1>
<P1>b) Whether the Minister properly included $168,302 in the Appellant's income in the 2008 taxation year under section 9(1) of the <EM>Act</EM>.</P1></P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>C.</N><TI>STATUTORY PROVISIONS RELIED ON</TI>
<P>13. He relies on sections 3, 9, 18, 20, 152, 153 of the <EM>Income Tax Act</EM>, R.S.C. 1985, c. 1 (5th Supp.), as amended (the &ldquo;<EM>Act</EM>&rdquo;) and Regulation 200 of the <EM>Income Tax Regulations</EM>.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><N>D.</N><TI>GROUNDS RELIED ON AND RELIEF SOUGHT</TI>
<P>14. He respectfully submits that the Minister properly included $8,125 and $168,302 in the Appellant's income in the 2007 and 2008 taxation years, respectively, under section 9(1) of the <EM>Act</EM>.</P>
<P>He requests that the appeal be dismissed with costs.</P>
